Diabetes Random Forest Model

# front-matter
rm(list = ls()) #clear the workspace

library(tidymodels)  # for the tune package, along with the rest of tidymodels

# Helper packages
library(rpart.plot)  # for visualizing a decision tree
library(vip)         # for variable importance plots
library(ranger)
data(PimaIndiansDiabetes2, package = "mlbench")

diabetes <- na.omit(PimaIndiansDiabetes2)

diabetes <- as_tibble(diabetes)
class(diabetes)
[1] "tbl_df"     "tbl"        "data.frame"
diabetes
set.seed(123)
diabetes_split <- initial_split(diabetes, strata = diabetes)
diabetes_train <- training(diabetes_split)
diabetes_test <- testing(diabetes_split)
# training set proportions by children
diabetes_train %>% 
  count(diabetes) %>% 
  mutate(prop = n/sum(n))

# test set proportions by children
diabetes_test  %>% 
  count(diabetes) %>% 
  mutate(prop = n/sum(n))
tune_spec <- rand_forest(
                trees = tune(),
                min_n = tune()
              ) %>%
             set_engine("ranger", importance = "impurity") %>%
             set_mode("classification")

tune_spec
Random Forest Model Specification (classification)

Main Arguments:
  trees = tune()
  min_n = tune()

Engine-Specific Arguments:
  importance = impurity

Computational engine: ranger 
forest_grid <- grid_regular(
                          trees(),
                          min_n(),
                          levels = 10)

forest_grid
forest_grid %>%
  count(trees)
set.seed(234)
diabetes_folds <- vfold_cv(diabetes_train)
diabetes_folds
#  10-fold cross-validation 
set.seed(345)

forest_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(tune_spec) %>%
  add_formula(diabetes ~ .)

forest_res <-
  forest_wf %>%
  tune_grid(
      resamples = diabetes_folds,
      grid = forest_grid,
      control = control_grid(save_pred = TRUE),
      metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
      )

forest_res
# Tuning results
# 10-fold cross-validation 
forest_res %>%
  collect_metrics
#tree_res %>%
  #collect_metrics() %>%
  #mutate(tree_depth = factor(tree_depth)) %>%
  #ggplot(aes(cost_complexity, mean, color = tree_depth)) +
  #geom_line(size = 1.5, alpha = 0.6) +
  #geom_point(size = 2) +
  #facet_wrap(~ .metric, scales = "free", nrow = 2) +
  #scale_x_log10(labels = scales::label_number()) +
  #scale_color_viridis_d(option = "plasma", begin = .9, end = 0)
forest_res %>%
  show_best("roc_auc")
best_forest <- forest_res %>%
  select_best("roc_auc")

best_forest
rf_auc <-
  forest_res %>%
  collect_predictions(parameters = best_forest) %>%
  roc_curve(diabetes, .pred_neg) %>%
  mutate(model = "Random Forest")

autoplot(rf_auc)


library(data.table)
fwrite(rf_auc,'/Users/malcolmzerbe/practice_r/diabetes/project/volume/data/processed/rf_auc.csv')
rf_final_wf <-
  forest_wf %>%
  finalize_workflow(best_forest)

rf_final_wf

  min_n = 14

rf_final_fit <-
  rf_final_wf %>%
  last_fit(diabetes_split)

rf_final_fit %>%
  collect_metrics

rf_final_fit %>% collect_predictions()
rf_final_fit %>%
  collect_predictions() %>%
  roc_curve(diabetes, .pred_neg) %>%
  autoplot()

final_forest <- extract_workflow(rf_final_fit)
final_forest
